@Domenic - L-DOPA is not merely a drug; it is synthesized naturally in many organisms, including humans. When it is used as a drug, it is given the name levodopa. 

It is involved in many, many things in the biological world, including being part of the mechanism of byssal thread polymerization in my cousins, the mussel. (Those are the threads by which mussels attach to rocks, pilings, boat hulls, etc...)

If you are unfamiliar with it, you might want to check out the movie Awakenings, which is based upon the book of the same name by Oliver Sacks, who first used it to treat people in comas induced by encephalitis.  If you view/read the movie/book, you will never forget L-DOPA. The movie has a relatively high rating on IMDB (7.8) and stars Robin Williams and Robert De Niro.

